explains: adj. 发达的；发育良好的

sentences.en: Between the older layers of glacial material were well-developed soils containing fossils of warm-climate plants.
sentences.cn: 较古老的冰川物质层之间是发育良好的土壤，它含有（生活在）温暖气候中的植物的化石。

sentences.en: Mae La Na is a relatively modern and well-developed village, but tourists still have more than enough possibilities to experience an authentic way of living.
sentences.cn: 湄拉娜是一个相对现代和发达的村庄，但旅客们仍能有丰富的机会来体验真实的生活方式。

sentences.en: Horses have a well-developed instinct for fear.
